• The second depreciation record (“Depreciation20240201002”) has an amount of 45,741.88.

Because there is no accumulated depreciation carried in from a previous period (i.e. the beginning “accumulated depreciation” is assumed 0.00), the accumulated depreciation “end value” is the sum of the depreciation recorded during the period:

  45,746.47 + 45,741.88 = 91,488.35

Thus, the accumulated depreciation initial value is 0.00 and the end value is 91,488.35.
